## What I Am Still Thinking About

One thing I am not fully clear on yet: how do organizations realistically maintain the monitoring step over time? Step 7 implies continuous reassessment — but in a resource-constrained environment, continuous monitoring can be expensive and labor-intensive.

Is there a practical threshold for how often controls should be reassessed? Does it depend on the risk level of the system? I imagine the answer involves some combination of automated monitoring tools and scheduled manual reviews — but I want to understand what that looks like in a real healthcare environment. Something to dig into further.

